The paper deals with the capacity of a discrete memoryless channel with feedback, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The concept of listsizes is also relevant to source coding (cs.SI) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of feedback in communication systems is a topic in networking (cs.NI). Finally, the paper explores relationships to other notions of channel capacity, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
